Russian Wheat Production May Rise to 54 Million Tons, USDA Says

-- B y   J e f f   W i l s o n
-- 
2011-08-03T19:26:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/russian-wheat-production-may-rise-to-54-million-tons-usda-says.html
Russia may harvest 54 million metric
tons of wheat in the year that began July 1, up from 41.508
million a year earlier, a unit of the  U.S. Department of
Agriculture  said in a  report  posted today on its website.
Exports may rise to 14 million tons from 3.95 million last year.  In the season that started July 1, barley production may
almost double to 16.5 million tons, while exports may rise to 1
million tons from an estimated 300,000 a year earlier, the
